  "text": "This has been demonstrated in the postural control system by examining the body's centerof-pressure (COP) excursions while standing on a force plate [CITATION_1] . Under normal circumstances, the COP time series exhibits 1/f behaviour, characteristic of pink noise. However, with the loss of vision, sensation in the feet, or both, there is a progressive loss of complexity and long-range correlations in the data. As a result, the individual has more difficulty adapting to a superimposed cognitive task (e.g., counting backwards while standing) and postural sway increases [CITATION_2] .",
